BENIN  – Josemaria Escriva Founda­tion (JOSEF) has embarked on an enlightenment cam­paign to sensitize and educate the youths on participatory democracy at the communi­ty levels. The programme, which is tagged: “Empowering the Youths to Stimulate Partic­ipatory Democracy at the Community Levels in Edo State”, is being organised under the agents for Citi­zen-Driven Transformation (ACT) programme, financed by the European Union and implemented by the British Council in collaboration with the Josemaria Escriva Foundation based in Ekpoma, headquarters of Esan West lo­cal government area of Edo State. The project will be carried out in the five local govern­ment areas of the Edo Central Senatorial District.